<div class="markdown"><h1>Linear model fitting</h1>
<p>This is an example tutorial showing how to fit a linear model with <a href="https://juliastats.org/GLM.jl">GLM.jl</a> and plot it with <a href="https://makie.juliaplots.org/stable/">Makie.jl</a>.</p>
</div>


<div class="markdown"><p>Let&#39;s start by generating the linear relationship</p>
<p class="tex">$$y &#61; 2x &#43; \epsilon,$$</p>
<p>where <span class="tex">$\epsilon$</span> is random noise.</p>
</div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>using DataFrames</code></pre>


<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>df = let
    X = 1:100
    Y = [2x + rand(1:20) for x in X]
    DataFrame(; X, Y)
end</code></pre>

<div class="markdown"><p>In a plot, the data looks as follows:</p>
</div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>using CairoMakie</code></pre>


<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>lines(df.X, df.Y)</code></pre>
<img src="data:image/png;base64,">


<div class="markdown"><p>On this data, a linear model can be fitted:</p>
</div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>using GLM</code></pre>


<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>model = lm(@formula(Y ~ X), df);</code></pre>



<div class="markdown"><p>Which gives estimates for the intercept and slope:</p>
</div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>intercept, slope = GLM.coef(model)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-intercept' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>2-element Vector{Float64}:
 10.111515151515226
  2.0045244524452435</pre>


<div class="markdown"><p>With this, we can determine all values which are &quot;predicted&quot; by the fitted model:</p>
</div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>Y_fitted = [intercept + slope * x for x in df.X];</code></pre>



<div class="markdown"><p>And plot it again:</p>
</div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>let
    fig = Figure()
    ax = Axis(fig[1, 1])

    lines!(ax, df.X, df.Y, label="true")
    lines!(ax, df.X, Y_fitted; color=:black, linestyle=:dash, label="fitted")

    axislegend(ax; position=:lt)
    fig
end</code></pre>
